article.headline: Sacramento State 57, Montana 54
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- DaShawn Freeman had 25 points, 10 steals, and nine assists to help Sacramento State beat Montana 83-80 Thursday night. Jameel Pugh added 25 points and seven rebounds for fourth-place Sacramento State (10-15, 6-6), which needs one more win in the conference to clinch its third-consecutive Big Sky tournament appearance. The top six teams make the conference tournament. Kamarr Davis had 26 points, and Andrew Strait and Lamarr Farr each had 12 for the Grizzlies (12-12, 6-5), who remained in third place in the conference. With the game tied at 75 with 26 seconds to play, Sacramento State's Jason Harris and DaShawn Freeman hit four throws each to seal the victory. Montana was leading 35-24 in the first half until Sacramento State came back to take the lead 42-41 after Jameel Pugh hit a 3-point shot with 2:07 remaining. Montana reclaimed the lead on the next possession on John Seyfert's basket and the Grizzlies ended the half leading 44-42. Montana shot 58 percent (18-for-31) in the first half while the Hornets, who hit six 3-pointers, shot 44 percent (16-for-36) from the floor. Montana, who committed 23 turnovers, shot 59 percent (32-for-54) from the floor. The Hornets committed 10 turnovers while shooting 44 percent (29-for-69) from the field.
